[b][u]What is a Form?[/b]
A form is basically an easy way to set-up your scripts. It provides a user-friendly interface where you can type in all your information.

[b][u][size=20pt]Chapter 1 â€“ Lets create a form (Beginner)[/b]
[u]Requirements[/u]
Some basic SCAR knowledge required.

[u]Overview[/u]
In Chapter 1, we will be making a Form that saves our Username and Password. You will learn how to create â€“ Labels, Edit boxes and Buttons.

[b][u]Getting started[/b]
What we will need to do is open the Form editor in SCAR. You can do this by going Tools -> Form Editor. Once that is open, 3 boxes should appear.

[b][u]Labels[/b]
Now on the top box, click on the â€˜Aâ€™ then click anywhere on the Blank form(preferably towards the left). Now we must change the name.

Eg.[img]http://img98.imageshack.us/img98/1938/form1jc5.jpg[/img]


Now create another label for the password.

[b][u]Edit boxes[/b]
Now that we have created the labels, we need some boxes for the user to add text in.
Click on the box next to the Label one and make a click next to the Username and Password box. You may remove the caption.

Eg.[img]http://img96.imageshack.us/img96/7673/form2zr5.jpg[/img]

[b][u]Start Button[/b]
Now we got the Hard stuff out the way it's time to add a button so when you click, the Form will close. A couple of spaces to the right of the "Edit" button should be a box with the word "OK" in it. Click on that then click where you want your button to be. I'd personally put it the start button at the bottom, but it's your choice.

Eg.[img]http://img87.imageshack.us/img87/9291/form3qd1.jpg[/img]

[b][u]Resizing and changing the name[/b]
Resize the window to whatever fits best.

Now click on the icon that looks like this:
[img]http://img97.imageshack.us/img97/3600/form4pf3.jpg[/img]

Now click click anywhere on the for(Not on the buttons or labels) then change the Caption.

Eg.[img]http://img224.imageshack.us/img224/2268/form5ku0.jpg[/img]

[b][u]Implementing the form into the script[/b]
Save it by pressing the save icon then close the form editor.

Now we go to:
Tools -> Load DFM form

Then click on the form that you just saved. You should get a bunch of lines. Add the files that it says to the variables.

Eg.[code]var
  frmDesign : TForm;
  Label1 : TLabel;
  Label2 : TLabel;
  Edit2 : TEdit;
  Edit1 : TEdit;
  Button1 : TButton;[/code]

Now create a new procedure called â€œInitFormâ€ then paste all those lines above the var into it.

Eg.[code]program FormBegginerTutorial;
var
  frmDesign : TForm;
  Label1 : TLabel;
  Label2 : TLabel;
  Edit2 : TEdit;
  Edit1 : TEdit;
  Button1 : TButton;

procedure InitForm;
begin
  frmDesign := CreateForm;
  frmDesign.Left := 250;
  frmDesign.Top := 114;
  frmDesign.Width := 263;
  frmDesign.Height := 180;
  frmDesign.Caption := 'User and Pass Saver';
  frmDesign.Color := clBtnFace;
  frmDesign.Font.Color := clWindowText;
  frmDesign.Font.Height := -11;
  frmDesign.Font.Name := 'MS Sans Serif';
  frmDesign.Font.Style := [];
  frmDesign.Visible := True;
  frmDesign.PixelsPerInch := 96;
  Label1 := TLabel.Create(frmDesign);
  Label1.Parent := frmDesign;
  Label1.Left := 32;
  Label1.Top := 40;
  Label1.Width := 51;
  Label1.Height := 13;
  Label1.Caption := 'Username:';
  Label2 := TLabel.Create(frmDesign);
  Label2.Parent := frmDesign;
  Label2.Left := 33;
  Label2.Top := 65;
  Label2.Width := 49;
  Label2.Height := 13;
  Label2.Caption := 'Password:';
  Edit2 := TEdit.Create(frmDesign);
  Edit2.Parent := frmDesign;
  Edit2.Left := 93;
  Edit2.Top := 37;
  Edit2.Width := 121;
  Edit2.Height := 21;
  Edit2.TabOrder := 8;
  Edit1 := TEdit.Create(frmDesign);
  Edit1.Parent := frmDesign;
  Edit1.Left := 93;
  Edit1.Top := 62;
  Edit1.Width := 121;
  Edit1.Height := 21;
  Edit1.TabOrder := 9;
  Button1 := TButton.Create(frmDesign);
  Button1.Parent := frmDesign;
  Button1.Left := 79;
  Button1.Top := 99;
  Button1.Width := 75;
  Button1.Height := 25;
  Button1.Caption := 'Start!';
  Button1.TabOrder := 10;
end;

begin
end.[/code]

Now we will add three more procedures.

[code]procedure SafeInitForm;
var
  v: TVariantArray;
begin
  setarraylength(V, 0);
  ThreadSafeCall('InitForm', v);
end;

procedure ShowFormModal;
begin
  frmDesign.ShowModal;
end;

procedure SafeShowFormModal;
var
  v: TVariantArray;
begin
  setarraylength(V, 0);
  ThreadSafeCall('ShowFormModal', v);
end;[/code]
These procedures are just to make sure that the form will not freeze.

Add these two lines to your main begin.
[code]begin
  SafeInitForm;
  SafeShowFormModal;
  FreeForm(frmDesign); // Frees the form from memory.
end.[/code]

Now we will need to remove the form visibility.
Find the line that looks like this.
[code]frmDesign.Visible := True;[/code]
And change it to this
[code]frmDesign.Visible := False;[/code]

Now we are basically done.

In the "InitForm" procedure look for the the button lines.
You should find something like this:
[code]  Button1 := TButton.Create(frmDesign);
  Button1.Parent := frmDesign;
  Button1.Left := 79;
  Button1.Top := 99;
  Button1.Width := 75;
  Button1.Height := 25;
  Button1.Caption := 'Start!';
  Button1.TabOrder := 10;[/code]
Change it to
[code]  Button1 := TButton.Create(frmDesign);
  Button1.Parent := frmDesign;
  Button1.OnClick := @ButtonClick;
  Button1.Left := 79;
  Button1.Top := 99;
  Button1.Width := 75;
  Button1.Height := 25;
  Button1.Caption := 'Start!';
  Button1.TabOrder := 10;[/code]

This will call the procedure "ButtonClick" when the button is clicked.

[b][u]Making the start button useful[/b]
Lets create a new procedure above InitForm.
[code]procedure ButtonClick(sender: TObject);
begin
end;[/code]

Now lets make the button close when we click it. Add the following lines of scar to your buttonclick procedure.
[code]  WriteLn('You have clicked the button');
  frmDesign.Caption:= frmDesign.Caption + '.';
  frmDesign.ModalResult:= mrOk;[/code]

You should now have something like this:
[code]program FormBegginerTutorial;
var
